# Rust
/target
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.orig

# B2's disposable index — a pure projection of the Markdown, never authoritative.
# Drop it and `b2 reindex` rebuilds it identical, so it must never be committed.
.b2/

# SQLite scratch / WAL sidecars from ad-hoc runs
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-wal
*.sqlite-shm

# Frontend (ui/) — npm deps + the Vite build output. The bundle is generated from
# src/, so it's never committed (the Tauri host embeds ui/dist at build time).
ui/node_modules/
ui/dist/

# Tauri generated artifacts (schemas, gen/) under the desktop host crate.
crates/b2-desktop/gen/

# macOS
.DS_Store

# local logs
/logs/
# don't ignore logs/.keep
!/logs/.keep

# The retrieval eval's append-only results log (the eval harness, crates/b2-embed/evals/): one JSON
# line per scored run, machine-local (scores depend on the machine's model/device).
crates/b2-embed/evals/results.jsonl

# Embed device-compare (scripts/compare-embed-device.sh) artifacts. Its work copies live in
# the system tempdir and its logs land under logs/ above — both already covered — but pin the
# footgun explicitly: an ad-hoc `b2 reindex` pointed straight at the committed test vault would
# drop a disposable index here (also matched by the global `.b2/` rule; listed for clarity).
fixtures/test-vault/.b2/
logs/embed-compare-*.jsonl
